<head>RUINS</head><list type="altnames">
<item>RUIN</item></list><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">廢墟 </item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BUILDING OR BUILDINGS that have been COMPLETELY DESTROYED.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current standard word for ruins is xū 墟 / 虛.</p>
<p>2. Qiū 丘 "mound" is sometimes used periphrastically to refer to ruins.</p></div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>廢墟</p>
<p>遺跡</p>
<p>芳躅</p>
<p>雪泥鴻爪</p>
<p>瓦礫 refers generally to rubble or debris and is perhaps marginal in the series.</p>
<p>斷垣殘壁</p>
<p>殘垣斷壁</p>
<p>斷井頹垣</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div>
